<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000046#     2#          453#">Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-453</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_46.2-453"/><heading><desig>§ 46.2-453.</desig><title>Proof of financial responsibility by delivering cash or securities</title></heading><bodyText><p>A person may give proof of financial responsibility by delivering to the Commissioner cash or securities equal to the sum of the liability coverage required for bodily injury or death of two or more persons in any one accident and injury to or destruction of property of others in any one accident as prescribed by <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 46.2-472"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-472">§ 46.2-472<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000046#     2#          472#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>. Securities so deposited shall be such as public bodies may invest in according to <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 2.2-4500"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 2.2-4500">§ 2.2-4500<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000002#     2#         4500#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 46-474; 1954, c. 378; 1958, cc. 501, 541, § 46.1-485; 1968, c. 685; 1978, c. 220; 1980, c. 484; 1986, c. 16; <ci